Class BookableRoom

java.lang.Object
BookableRoom
public class BookableRoom
extends java.lang.Object
Represents a bookable room within the booking system A bookable room is a Room anchored in time that can be used in a booking, in order to schedule and take a covid test in
Since:
1.0

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors 
    Constructor Description
    BookableRoom​(BookableRoom bookableRoom)
    Creates a bookable room Creates a clone of a bookable room, copying all of its attributes, but being stored in a different memory location
    BookableRoom​(java.lang.String code, int capacity, java.lang.String date)
    Creates a bookable room Sets the bookable rooms status as empty, since it is just created and cannot be full The occupancy is 0 for the same reason
    BookableRoom​(Room room, java.lang.String date, int occupancy)
    Creates a bookable room Takes in an existing room containing a code and capacity This takes in an occupancy so that the initial data can be changed to have an available and a full room, otherwise a new bookable room would be set to an empty status with an occupancy of 0 To ensure that happens each time use the previous constructor with parameters code, capacity, date
